      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "I think if you create the (datadir)/wallets directory manually and move your wallets into it, bitcoin should use this location, even on windows. For backwards compatibility, bitcoin will not create a (datadir)/wallets directory unless the entire datadir is new. But if the directory exists, it should use it regardless of platform. From `-help` output:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  -walletdir=<dir>\r\n       Specify directory to hold wallets (default: <datadir>/wallets if it\r\n       exists, otherwise <datadir>)\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
